	• Tutorials and Documentation:
		○ https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/workspaces
	
	• Workspace concept:
		○ A workspace is like a project level grouping, with folders and files below that in hierarchy
		○ Think of a workspace as the root of a project that has extra VS Code knowledge and capabilities.
		
	• Workspace settings
		○ In settings, you can toggle between user and workspace
		○ The user settings are the global settings
		○ Workspace settings enable you to configure settings in the context of the workspace you have opened and always override global user settings.
		○ 

	• Remove folders from workspace:
 just go to command palate and type workspaces:remove and then remove them
